   614	The dominant sensitivity is not a parameter but a philosophy. At the near-RCT-only floor —
   615	non-randomized tiers shrunk to a credibility mean of 0.01, the randomized tier kept at its drafted
   616	mean — the median collapses to 9,114 QALYs, dominated by the randomized-tier mental-health
   617	bucket; at near face value (all tier means 0.999) it rises to 414,264 (Figure 2). That 45-fold
   618	range exceeds the spread from any single distributional parameter — though structural choices
   619	can move the headline more: with no geographic repricing at all, every health dollar at U.S.
   620	anchors, the median is roughly 70,000 (the pre-correction model in the §5.3 table), so the routing
   621	assumption alone spans ~3× — and the gap between the face-value and best-guess estimates is
   622	a direct reading of how much of the estimated impact rests on evidence below randomized or
   623	strong quasi-experimental identification standards. The Spearman tornado (Figure 3) tells the
   624	same story within the default stance: the top three drivers are the global-health allocation share,
   625	the realization factor, and global-health credibility.
