   710	7 Limitations
   711	The credibility tiers and realization distribution are judgment priors with no literature calibration;
   712	the ordering is defensible, the levels are not measured, and the stance sweep is the honest bound
   713	on their influence. The QALY lens counts only health, so the estimate is a partial accounting
   714	that omits both the non-health benefits where Scott concentrates — education, mobility, equity
   715	— and any possible harms; it is not a floor on total wellbeing. Credibility shrinks toward zero
   716	but never below it, so the model places no mass on harmful giving; the closest available zero
   717	scenario is the near-RCT-only stance floor, which drives unsupported archetypes to ~1% credit.
   718	Allocation splits each organization’s dollars equally across its focus areas and service locations;
   719	both are coarse, and the geography audit covers only the 50 largest “global”-listed organizations.
   720	Realization is one global draw, so it cannot vary by cause. Archetype anchors treat heterogeneous
   721	organizations as draws from one distribution. Within each cause, delivery regions are priced
   722	identically, so the geographic decomposition exposes assumptions rather than measuring regional
   723	differences. The undisclosed third of dollars is imputed from a fitted elasticity, not observed. The
   724	routed global-health bucket prices its unattributable and high-income-region dollars — roughly a
   725	fifth of the bucket — at low-and-middle-income anchors, an upward-bias channel. Several cost
   726	priors average over mixed null-and-positive evidence before the credibility discount applies, so
   727	the two-multiplier separation of doubts is imperfect at those boundaries. The Dirichlet allocation
   728	spread is a subjective prior; uncertainty from the elasticity fit, unmatched filings, the focus-area
   729	crosswalk, and the geography audit is not propagated. Allocation shares are derived in nominal
   730	dollars and applied to the real total; re-deriving in real dollars moves shares by hundredths of a
   731	percentage point. The geography audit’s scalar U.S. shares and regional decompositions were
   732	reconciled separately and can differ by fractions of a point per organization. Finally, several
   733	anchors rest on a small number of quasi-experimental papers whose external validity to Scott’s
   734	grantees is exactly what the realization factor is guessing at.
