   608	The dominant sensitivity is not a parameter but a philosophy. At the near-RCT-only floor —
   609	non-randomized tiers shrunk to a credibility mean of 0.01, the randomized tier kept at its drafted
   610	mean — the median collapses to 9,114 QALYs, dominated by the randomized-tier mental-health
   611	bucket; at near face value (all tier means 0.999) it rises to 414,264 (Figure 2). That 45-fold range
   612	exceeds the spread from any single distributional parameter — though structural choices can
   613	move the headline more; the geographic-routing correction alone tripled it — and the gap between
   614	the face-value and best-guess estimates is a direct reading of how much of the estimated impact
   615	rests on evidence below randomized or strong quasi-experimental identification standards. The
   616	Spearman tornado (Figure 3) tells the same story within the default stance: the top three drivers
   617	are the global-health allocation share, the realization factor, and global-health credibility.
