# Neutrality review — round 3

| Round-2 item | Status | Verification against fresh text |
|---:|---|---|
| 4 | NOT RESOLVED | §5.1 is still headed “Evidence philosophy dominates everything else,” while the paragraph immediately concedes that structural choices can move the headline more. The abstract and body remain appropriately narrowed to the tested single-parameter sensitivities, but the heading retains the overstatement. Rename it along the lines of “Evidence stance dominates single-parameter sensitivity.” |
| 7 | RESOLVED | §4.2 deletes the unsupported full-scale universal and now limits the directional claim to “any scale the cited benchmarks speak to.” This matches the evidence and preserves the stated scarcity/attainability caveat. |

## New findings

None. A brief regression review of the newest edits found no new neutrality problem. The revised priority, regional-classification, structural-sensitivity, audit, limitations, and transferability language is appropriately qualified for an SSRN working paper.

RECOMMENDATION: Minor revisions

